main event: A witness in Columbus, Ohio observed a bright, round, whitish object moving overhead at a high rate of speed on July 31, 1961.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a solid object, but did not have any visible wings or appendages.
The object remained visible for 2-3 minutes before disappearing from view.
The witness could not conclusively identify the nature of the object, but it exhibited characteristics consistent with an aircraft or other man-made craft.
Multiple residents in the area reported seeing similar unidentified objects in the sky.
The witness filled out a detailed questionnaire as part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation of unidentified aerial phenomena.
